    "Clinical_Features": {
      "text": "Pruritic\ngeneralized vesicular exanthem with mild systemic manifestations\nUsually affects children <10y",
      "subsections": {
        "Rash": {
          "text": "Starts on trunk or scalp as pruritic, red macules, spreads to extremities\nWithin 24hr rash becomes vesicular (on erythematous base)\nOften referred to as \"dew drop on a rose petal\"\n[1]\nPalms/soles spared\nLesions in various stages of development\nThe number of lesions can vary; usually 300 or less but can be more than 2,000\n[1]",
          "tables": []
        },
        "Complications": {
          "text": "Can include\nencephalitis\n,\notitis media\n,\npneumonia\n,\nhepatitis\n,\nstrep\n/\nstaph\nsuperinfection\nof ruptured vesicles\nPerinatal infection in neonates may develop serious illness",
          "tables": []
        }
      },
